{"body": "> Personally, I'm against merging this because there may be some apps out there that are returning false without realising it due to ruby's implicit return feature\r\n\r\nI ask myself if this would really be a problem in practice. I mean, in order to break a production app, people would have to return `false`  in a `before_add` block, upgrade Rails without checking what has changed and how that could affect their application, and then not execute their tests, or execute their tests with an insufficient coverage.\r\n\r\n+1 on @shwoodard's @brianmario's and @pdelanauze's points.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/5112120", "created_at": "2012-04-13T10:29:26Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2881#issuecomment-5112120", "updated_at": "2012-04-13T10:29:26Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 2881, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KlausTrainer/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KlausTrainer/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KlausTrainer/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/KlausTrainer", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KlausTrainer/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/KlausTrainer", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KlausTrainer/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/6ed1a9b7f7d696817c0e716162f26abd?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F39b998ae413916c731157826a5fda213.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KlausTrainer/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KlausTrainer/received_events", "gravatar_id": "6ed1a9b7f7d696817c0e716162f26abd", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KlausTrainer/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "KlausTrainer", "type": "User", "id": 230061, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KlausTrainer/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52383e10bd3543c151010560"}, "id": 5112120, "i